  "Simplify: (1 - cos²x) / sin x.": "",
  "tan x": "",
  "csc x": "",
  "Since 1 - cos²x = sin²x by the Pythagorean identity, we get sin²x / sin x = sin x.": "",
  "What is cos(A + B) equal to?": "",
  "cos A cos B + sin A sin B": "",
  "sin A cos B - cos A sin B": "",
  "cos A cos B - sin A sin B": "",
  "sin A cos B + cos A sin B": "",
  "The cosine addition formula states cos(A + B) = cos A cos B - sin A sin B. Note the subtraction sign, which distinguishes it from cos(A - B).": "",
  "Which is a valid form of the double-angle formula for cos 2x?": "",
  "sin²x + cos²x": "",
  "1 - 2sin²x": "",
  "2cos x - 1": "",
  "cos 2x has three equivalent forms: cos²x - sin²x, 2cos²x - 1, and 1 - 2sin²x. The option 1 - 2sin²x is one of these valid forms.": "",
  "Simplify: sec x · cos x.": "",
  "0": "",
  "Since sec x = 1/cos x, multiplying sec x by cos x gives (1/cos x)(cos x) = 1. Secant and cosine are reciprocal functions.": "",
