  "V = sin²x": "",
  "V = cos 2x": "",
  "The double-angle identity states sin 2x = 2 sin x cos x. Therefore V = 2 sin x cos x simplifies directly to V = sin 2x.": "",
  "A surveyor measures an angle x in Quadrant II where sin x = 5/13. She needs to calculate sin 2x for her report. What value should she record?": "",
  "-60/169": "",
  "60/169": "",
  "-120/169": "",
  "120/169": "",
  "In Q II, cos x is negative. cos x = -12/13 (from sin²x + cos²x = 1). sin 2x = 2 sin x cos x = 2(5/13)(-12/13) = -120/169.": "",
  "A robotics programmer needs the exact value of cos 15° for a motor calibration. Using the difference formula cos(45° - 30°), what should she enter?": "",
  "√3/4": "",
  "(√3 + 1)/2": "",
